The paper deals with a coloring process in a graph, which is a fundamental topic in graph theory and discrete mathematics. The concept of irreversible dynamic monopolies is a specific problem related to graph coloring. Therefore, cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves analyzing the size of the irreversible dynamos, which is related to graph theory and combinatorics, making cs.GT (Graph Theory) a likely category as well. The paper also discusses the complexity of finding the minimum irreversible dynamo, which is a computational problem, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) possible categories.
